         </tr> 
         <tr> 
          <td align="center" bgcolor="#373737" height="30" style="border-top: 1px solid #FFFFFF" valign="middle" width="588"> 
           <table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="588"> 
            <tbody> 
             <tr> 
              <td height="10" width="20"><img alt="spacer.gif" height="10" src="https://img.verticalresponse.com/email_layout/3257/spacer.gif" style="display: block; width: 20px; height: 10px;" width="20"></td> 
              <td align="left" style=" text-decoration: none; padding-left: 0; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 0; padding-bottom: 10px;"> 
               <div style="margin: 0 0 0 0; color: #FFFFFF; line-height: 11px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px">
                <a href="#" style="text-decoration: none; color: #ffffff;">Issue 8&nbsp;| August/September&nbsp;201</a>4&nbsp;&nbsp;
               </div> </td> 
              <td align="right" style=" padding-left: 10px; padding-top: 10px; padding-right: 10px; padding-bottom: 10px;" width="200"> 
               <div style="margin: 0 0 0 0; color: #FFFFFF; line-height: 11px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px">
                <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/"><span style="color:#FFFFFF;">www.iris.edu</span></a>
               </div> </td> 
             </tr> 
            </tbody> 
           </table> </td> 
         </tr> 
         <tr> 
          <td align="center" valign="top" width="100%"> 
           <table align="center" border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="588"> 
            <tbody> 
             <tr> 
              <td align="left" style="padding: 0px 40px 0px 0px; text-align: left;" valign="top" width="418"> 
               <div style="line-height: 24px; margin: 0px 0px 10px; color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 24px;">
                <br> 
                <span style="color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 24px; line-height: 24px;">IRIS Facilities Contribute&nbsp;<br> to iMUSH</span>
                <br> 
                <img align="none" alt="iMUSH_web" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/8c97a57ead/iMUSH_web.jpg" style="width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="iMUSH_web" vspace="10" width="371">
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Imaging Magma Under St. Helens (</span>
                <a href="http://imush.org" style="font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">iMUSH</a>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">) is a four-year collaborative study&nbsp;that is being conducted&nbsp;by several IRIS Consortium members. The </span>
                <a href="http://www.nsf.gov" style="font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">NSF</a>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">-funded project is&nbsp;using&nbsp;multiple geophysical and geological techniques to investigate&nbsp;the volcano's plumbing system,&nbsp;including 70&nbsp;passive long-term seismographs&nbsp;and a&nbsp;2500-site deployment of short-term seismographs for a controlled-source experiment--&nbsp;all&nbsp;borrowed from the IRIS </span>
                <a href="http://www.passcal.nmt.edu/" style="font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">PASSCAL</a>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"> and USArray </span>
                <a href="http://www.usarray.org/researchers/obs/flexible" style="font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">Flexible Array</a>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;"> instrument </span>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">pools</span>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">. Illustrating how a new generation of instrumentation is transforming seismology by enabling </span>
                <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/wavefields" style="font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">recording of well-sampled wavefields</a>
                <span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 8pt; line-height: 11px; font-family: arial, helvetica, sans-serif;">, nearly 1000 additional autonomous nodes were added to record densely sampled data over a time period long enough for ambient noise analysis, while also improving use of the controlled-source shots. Photo of a node (yellow in foreground) by Steve Hansen, University of New Mexico.</span>
                <br> 
                <br> 
                <br> Advanced Studies Institute Trains Analysts in Colombia
               </div> 
               <div style="line-height: 0px;">
                <img align="none" alt="Bogota_newsletter" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/8c97a57ead/Bogota_newsletter.jpg" style="display: block; width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="Bogota_newsletter" vspace="10" width="371">
               </div> 
               <div style="line-height: 12px; color: rgb(71, 71, 71); font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif; font-size: 11px;"> 
                <div style="margin: 0 0 10px 0">
                 <span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="line-height: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">During early August, IRIS offered&nbsp;an <a href="http://www.iris.edu/ds/workshops/2014/08/advanced-studies-institute-on-earthquake-related-data-products/">Advanced Studies Institute on Earthquake-Related Data Products</a> in Bogota, Colombia, where analysts learned methods to compute earthquake locations and moment tensors. This ASI followed <a href="http://www.iris.edu/ds/workshops/2014/07/managing-data-from-seismic-networks/">Managing Data from Seismic Networks</a>, a workshop run by <a href="http://www.iris.edu/ds/">IRIS Data Services</a>, and leveraged skills learned there. Felix Waldhauser introduced double-difference methods for relative event relocation&nbsp;using his <a href="http://www.ldeo.columbia.edu/~felixw/hypoDD.html">HypoDD software</a>. Bob Herrmann introduced seismic moment tensor determination using his library of "<a href="http://www.eas.slu.edu/eqc/eqccps.html">Computer Programs in Seismology</a>" and&nbsp;broadband data from regional and global seismic stations. Ray Russo and Susan Beck also assisted at&nbsp;the ASI.&nbsp;Financial support for the ASI was provided by the <a href="http://www.nsf.gov">National Science Foundation</a>. Photo by Susan Beck, University of Arizona.</span><br> <br> <br> &nbsp;</span>
                 <br> 
                 <span style="color: rgb(26, 26, 26); font-size: 24px; line-height: 24px;">2014 USArray Short Course Aimed at Graduate Students<br> <img align="none" alt="short_course_newsletter 2" border="0" height="198" hspace="0" src="https://cc286088d6-custmedia.vresp.com/8c97a57ead/short_course_newsletter%202.jpg" style="width: 371px; height: 198px;" title="short_course_newsletter 2" vspace="10" width="371"></span>
                 <br> 
                 <br> 
                 <span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="line-height: 11px; color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">From August 4-8, 24 students and six organizing instructors gathered at Northwestern University for the annual USArray short course. This summer's course was aimed at early-year graduate students and those starting graduate programs this fall who have limited programming experience, tools for data access, or exposure to analytical methods in seismology. Throughout the week, six guest instructors helped lead discussions and exercises. Students familiarized themselves with the basics of the Unix environment and command-line coding;&nbsp;a variety of seismic data access methods;&nbsp;and simple software tools for processing, analyzing, and visualizing waveform data. Participants were supported by the&nbsp;<a href="http://www.nsf.gov">National Science&nbsp;Foundation</a> through an award to <a href="http://www.iris.edu">IRIS</a>. IRIS staff Andy Frassetto, Chad Trabant, and Danielle Sumy helped to organize the course and served as instructors.</span></span></span>
                </div> 
               </div> </td> 
              <td align="left" bgcolor="#cdde9f" style="padding: 15px 10px 10px; text-align: left;" valign="top" width="200"> 
               <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"> 
                <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                 <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                  <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                    <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/workshops/2014/10/amphibious_array_facility_workshop"><span style="font-size:10pt;"><strong style="line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><span style="color: rgb(75, 0, 130);">Amphibious Array Workshop</span></strong></span></a>
                   </div> 
                  </div> 
                  <div style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159); margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="line-height: 13px; margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                    <span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><strong>October 23–24, 2014</strong><br> Snowbird, UT<br> <br> The workshop will consider the future of the Amphibious Array of onshore and ocean bottom seismometers currently deployed as the Cascadia Initiative.<br> <br> <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/workshops/2014/10/amphibious_array_facility_workshop">Registration</a> closes September 30.</span></span></span>
                   </div> 
                  </div> 
                 </div> 
                </div> 
                <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                 <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;">
                  <br> 
                  <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLD4D607C2FA317E6D" style="line-height: 13px;"><span style="font-size: 10pt;"><strong style="line-height: 13px; color: rgb(75, 0, 130);"><span style="color:#4B0082;">IRIS Webinars</span></strong></span></a> 
                  <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                    <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                     <br> 
                     <span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><font color="#000000" style="line-height: 11px; font-size: 8pt;">** 9/10 <b>Ellen Syracuse</b>, Seismic Constraints on the Subduction Factory: From Global to Local Scales<br> ** 9/24 <strong>Michael Hubenthal</strong>, The Nature of Cognition as a Driver for (Re)designing Classroom Lectures<br> ** 10/8 <strong>Lars Ottemoller</strong>, Introduction to SEISAN</font><br> <br> <font color="#000000" style="line-height: 11px; font-size: 8pt;">Missed viewing a webinar? IRIS archives past webinars <a href="https://www.youtube.com/playlist?list=PLD4D607C2FA317E6D">here</a></font><font color="#000000" style="line-height: 13px; font-size: 10px;">.</font></span></span>
                     <br> 
                     <br> 
                     <br> 
                     <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/wavefields"><span style="font-size:10pt;"><font color="#4b0082"><span style="line-height: 13px;"><b>Recording the Full Seismic Wavefield</b></span></font></span></a>
                     <br style="background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);"> 
                     <br> 
                     <span style="font-size:8pt;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="line-height: 11px; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">IRIS is hosting a series of online workshops to gather input from the broader seismological community about the potential scientific benefits of densely sampled full-wavefield data. Workshops are divided by application and&nbsp;scale and are intended together to be inclusive. To participate in the virtual workshop or to view past workshops, go to&nbsp;the <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/wavefields">IRIS website</a>. Attendance is limited.</span></span></span>
                     <br> 
                     <br> 
                     <br> 
                     <span style="font-size:10pt;"><strong><a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/distinguished_lectureship"><span style="color:#4B0082;">Upcoming IRIS/SSA Distinguished Lectureship Public Lectures</span></a></strong></span>
                     <br> 
                     <br> 
                     <span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><span style="font-size:8pt;">**&nbsp;September&nbsp;23&nbsp;<strong>Meredith Nettles. </strong>Glacial Earthquakes: Using Seismic and GPS Observations to Map Changes in Glaciers and Ice Sheets Worldwide.&nbsp;New Mexico Museum of History and Science, Albuquerque, NM.</span><br> <br> <span style="font-size:8pt;">** October 14 </span><strong style="font-size: 8pt; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">Jean-Paul Ampeuro&nbsp;</strong><span style="font-size:8pt;">Earth's Cocktail Party: Deciphering the Physics of Earthquakes with Networks of Seismic Arrays.&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: 8pt; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">Noel Wein Public Library in Fairbanks, AK.</span><span style="font-size: 8pt; background-color: rgb(205, 222, 159);">&nbsp;</span></span>
                     <br> &nbsp;
                    </div> 
                   </div> 
                  </div> 
                 </div> 
                 <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px; font-family: Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif;"> 
                  <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;"> 
                   <div style="margin: 0px 0px 10px;">
                    <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/fundraisers/2014/david_simpson_fund_innovation/" style="font-size: 10px;"><span style="color:#4B0082;"><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">David Simpson Fund for Innovation</span></strong></span></a>
                    <br> 
                    <br> 
                    <span style="font-size: 8pt;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;">If you haven't already contributed, please consider&nbsp;joining the growing number of <a href="https://ssl.iris.edu/fundraisers/2014/david_simpson_fund_innovation/donate/report">people who are participating </a>in this important community project. Go to the IRIS website&nbsp;to&nbsp;<a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/fundraisers/2014/david_simpson_fund_innovation/">learn more</a> and to <a href="https://ssl.iris.edu/fundraisers/2014/david_simpson_fund_innovation/donate/">donate</a>.&nbsp;</span></span>
                    <br> 
                    <br> 
                    <br> 
                    <span style="font-size:10pt;"><a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/animations/"><font color="#4b0082"><b>Regional Tectonics Animations</b></font></a></span>
                    <br> 
                    <br> 
                    <span style="font-size: 8pt;"><span style="font-family:arial,helvetica,sans-serif;"><a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/animations/35">A South America&nbsp;regional tectonics animation</a> is part of a growing collection of animations available on the <a href="http://www.iris.edu/hq/programs/education_and_outreach/animations/">IRIS website</a>.</span></span>
